WEBVTT

00:10.378 --> 00:12.480
<i>Previously on</i> The Serpent Queen...

00:12.513 --> 00:13.748
I dreamt that Diane died.

00:15.516 --> 00:16.450
<i>And then what?</i>

00:16.484 --> 00:17.618
<i>Then Henri died.</i>

00:17.651 --> 00:19.220
Then you already
know the price.

00:19.253 --> 00:20.755
That is a price
I am not willing to pay.

00:20.788 --> 00:23.457
We're here on behalf
of our niece, Mary Stuart.

00:23.491 --> 00:25.493
The king has forgotten
her betrothal

00:25.526 --> 00:27.194
<i>to his son, the dauphin.</i>

00:27.228 --> 00:28.729
Francis will wed
when the time is right.

00:28.763 --> 00:30.398
When will that be?

00:30.431 --> 00:33.033
When I am good and ready!

00:33.067 --> 00:34.769
He does not believe
the marriage is a good match.

00:35.803 --> 00:37.104
What in God's name

00:37.138 --> 00:39.039
does Henri know
about a good marriage?

00:39.073 --> 00:41.542
You've kept me a boy
to suit your needs.

00:41.575 --> 00:43.711
If my love has done you harm,

00:43.744 --> 00:45.446
you must send me away.

00:45.479 --> 00:47.748
Madame de Poitiers
has business to discuss.

00:47.782 --> 00:50.584
The wedding of the dauphin
will go forth as planned.

00:50.618 --> 00:51.819
<i>And may I suggest we invite</i>

00:52.052 --> 00:53.621
the Holy Roman emperor
of Spain.

00:53.654 --> 00:55.556
Welcome the man against whom

00:55.589 --> 00:57.658
<i>both you and your father
fought multiple wars?</i>

00:57.691 --> 00:59.660
- Are you mad?
- France!

00:59.693 --> 01:01.328
Will you joust
in the ceremonies today?

01:01.362 --> 01:03.831
It would please me to see you
as you were when we first met.

01:05.266 --> 01:07.101
Tell him I saw it in a dream,
that he dies

01:07.134 --> 01:08.669
<i>on this course
unless he stops now.</i>

01:08.702 --> 01:09.770
Once more.

01:14.341 --> 01:16.444
You are evil,
just like they all say.

01:16.477 --> 01:18.446
Oh, come on. No one's watching.

01:18.479 --> 01:19.747
<i>Are you sure
you picked the right girl?</i>

01:19.780 --> 01:22.583
Because if you don't take care
of this soon,

01:22.616 --> 01:24.552
<i>Mary will certainly
find her own way</i>

01:24.585 --> 01:26.520
to remain Queen of France.

02:01.655 --> 02:03.190
You've got a visitor.

02:04.758 --> 02:06.727
Your Majesty.

02:10.631 --> 02:12.800
You were expecting
your mistress?

02:12.833 --> 02:14.468
She won't come for you,
but perhaps

02:14.502 --> 02:17.438
you've already
figured that out by now.

02:18.806 --> 02:20.441
Sit.

02:22.476 --> 02:26.780
I take it I am the last person
you expected to see?

02:26.814 --> 02:29.283
I was arrested
for entering your chambers

02:29.316 --> 02:30.384
without permission.

02:30.417 --> 02:31.852
I did not think
you would care much

02:31.886 --> 02:33.787
about my situation.

02:33.821 --> 02:36.557
No, but I do.

02:36.590 --> 02:38.792
Forgiveness is the basis
of God's word,

02:38.826 --> 02:40.694
especially for those
who've been led astray

02:40.728 --> 02:43.197
through no fault of their own.

02:43.230 --> 02:46.267
I suspect it was Catherine
who sent you to my chambers.

02:46.300 --> 02:49.904
As I suspect her dalliance
with the dark arts.

02:49.937 --> 02:51.805
What I lack is proof of either.

02:53.374 --> 02:55.943
Perhaps you could help me find
what I'm looking for.

02:57.177 --> 03:00.514
<i>I'm sure you've heard many
unflattering things about me.</i>

03:00.548 --> 03:02.416
<i>And now you wonder
if you can trust me.</i>

03:02.449 --> 03:05.319
I--I see your dilemma.

03:06.887 --> 03:10.524
But allow me to tell you
of my true nature...

03:10.558 --> 03:12.927
so that you might better decide

03:12.960 --> 03:14.562
which side
you would like to be on.

03:17.698 --> 03:19.466
I think if you had seen me
on my wedding day,

03:19.500 --> 03:21.502
you would begin to understand.

03:23.237 --> 03:26.206
It was a day I thought

03:26.240 --> 03:28.576
just as God had willed it.

03:30.444 --> 03:34.214
Until I realized
that there were other...

03:34.248 --> 03:36.650
darker forces at work.

03:38.652 --> 03:40.754
Henri!

03:45.626 --> 03:46.927
Henri.

03:46.961 --> 03:49.463
<i>King Henri's tragic
fall came as a surprise</i>

03:49.496 --> 03:51.332
<i>to all except one.</i>

04:05.846 --> 04:06.947
Don't try to speak.

04:08.616 --> 04:09.783
Protect my children.

04:09.817 --> 04:12.620
Protect my children
like you've protected me.

04:12.653 --> 04:14.588
You will be here
to protect them yourself.

04:14.622 --> 04:16.824
All right? You will be here.

04:18.392 --> 04:21.295
You haven't lost the ability
to lie, I see.

04:30.037 --> 04:31.572
Come on!

04:32.473 --> 04:33.440
Fetch it, now.

04:46.286 --> 04:47.421
Let me pass.

04:47.454 --> 04:49.923
Your presence is no longer
required, madam.

04:49.957 --> 04:51.058
He needs me.

04:51.291 --> 04:53.027
This is a family matter.

04:54.595 --> 04:55.929
Henri!

05:05.973 --> 05:07.808
No. Please no.

05:10.844 --> 05:13.681
Why did you not stop jousting
when I told you to?

05:13.714 --> 05:15.049
Why?

05:17.851 --> 05:18.886
Why?

05:20.054 --> 05:22.056
I wanted your dream
to come true.

05:22.089 --> 05:24.458
- <i>No.</i>
- Because I know wanted it to.

05:24.491 --> 05:25.559
No!

05:25.592 --> 05:27.327
I told you to stop!

05:29.596 --> 05:31.465
You should never have loved me.

05:31.498 --> 05:33.033
What?

05:34.935 --> 05:36.637
I love you still.

05:37.871 --> 05:38.872
Shh...

05:38.906 --> 05:42.409
Then I pity you... as a fool.

05:44.378 --> 05:48.482
A very unfortunate accident.

05:48.515 --> 05:50.684
And on your wedding day.

05:50.718 --> 05:52.653
A day that should
be filled with joy,

05:52.686 --> 05:56.123
now marred by tragedy.

05:56.356 --> 05:57.624
The king is strong.

05:57.658 --> 05:58.826
He is certain to survive.

05:58.859 --> 06:00.394
He has a pole in his eye.

06:02.029 --> 06:04.932
At a time like this, we should
take comfort in our faith.

06:04.965 --> 06:07.434
Perhaps a prayer?

06:07.468 --> 06:09.737
Yes. Yes.

06:09.770 --> 06:11.472
Lead us, Uncle?

06:11.505 --> 06:13.373
Of course.

06:13.407 --> 06:15.676
Though might not
our Bourbon brothers

06:15.709 --> 06:19.446
take offense
to our Catholic liturgy, hm?

06:19.480 --> 06:23.117
Uh, today I believe
we are all Frenchmen first.

06:23.150 --> 06:24.451
<i>Oh.</i>

06:25.452 --> 06:28.756
I'm very pleased
to hear you say so.

06:28.789 --> 06:30.090
In these times of darkness,

06:30.124 --> 06:34.628
we must all reach out
towards the light.

06:34.661 --> 06:36.997
For example,
I would be more than happy

06:37.030 --> 06:39.166
to promote an alliance
with France

06:39.399 --> 06:42.536
to secure the English throne.

06:43.637 --> 06:45.105
<i>If, God forbid,</i>

06:45.139 --> 06:47.074
the king does not
survive the night,

06:47.107 --> 06:49.409
and the new Queen...

06:49.443 --> 06:52.713
<i>of France and Scotland</i>

06:52.746 --> 06:57.718
<i>happens also to be
the rightful Queen of England.</i>

06:57.751 --> 06:59.153
You see?

06:59.186 --> 07:00.788
Would certainly be convenient.

07:00.821 --> 07:03.857
Ah. Let us kneel.

07:06.827 --> 07:07.895
Really?

07:07.928 --> 07:09.129
I'm not kneeling.

07:13.567 --> 07:15.068
How is my father?

07:15.102 --> 07:18.972
I'm afraid we cannot remove
the shrapnel from his eye

07:19.006 --> 07:20.974
without risking his life.

07:21.008 --> 07:22.676
It's all right. It's all right.
It's all right.

07:22.709 --> 07:24.044
It's all right, Francis.

07:24.077 --> 07:26.747
Take each breath slowly, yeah?

07:26.780 --> 07:29.082
Remember?
Like sipping cold water.

07:29.116 --> 07:31.485
I'm not ready, Mary.

07:31.518 --> 07:33.220
Francis, if it is God's will
for you to be king,

07:33.453 --> 07:35.589
you only have to trust in Him
to make you ready.

07:37.991 --> 07:39.526
We are by your side.

07:40.661 --> 07:42.062
Let us be
your pillars of strength.

07:42.095 --> 07:43.597
And faith.

07:43.630 --> 07:45.966
Lean on us, Francis,
and all will be fine.

07:45.999 --> 07:48.569
You... you can lean on us,
too, remember.

07:48.602 --> 07:51.839
Like a... like a chair.

07:51.872 --> 07:53.473
- A what?
- <i>We're like the...</i>

07:53.507 --> 07:55.609
the legs of a chair.

07:56.210 --> 07:57.678
To sit on, you know.

07:58.478 --> 08:00.180
Sturdy.

08:00.214 --> 08:02.049
Come with me.

08:03.617 --> 08:05.786
<i>Well, you certainly</i>

08:05.819 --> 08:07.521
couldn't have wished
for a better time

08:07.554 --> 08:09.156
to work your mischief,
could you?

08:09.189 --> 08:11.692
I merely play the pieces
as I find them.

08:11.725 --> 08:15.529
This is not a chessboard, Charles.

08:15.562 --> 08:17.664
These people happen
to be my family.

08:17.698 --> 08:19.266
And you cannot expect me
to participate

08:19.499 --> 08:20.968
in their destruction.

08:21.001 --> 08:23.270
But that's what families do.

08:23.503 --> 08:24.972
Bit by bit,

08:25.005 --> 08:26.106
then all at once.

08:26.139 --> 08:29.543
No one gets out alive.

08:29.576 --> 08:30.677
What is wrong with you?

08:32.846 --> 08:34.114
When you operate on the king,

08:34.147 --> 08:35.816
you must be sure
of the outcome.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.017
Of course.

08:37.050 --> 08:38.652
What are the charges?

08:41.655 --> 08:43.657
Murdered his mother
while she slept,

08:43.690 --> 08:47.227
set fire to his neighbor's
house over a financial dispute,

08:47.261 --> 08:49.730
<i>and impropriety with a child.</i>

08:50.564 --> 08:51.565
Start with him.

08:52.733 --> 08:53.800
No. No, no, no.

08:53.834 --> 08:54.902
No! No!

08:54.935 --> 08:56.837
<i>Wait. Wait!</i>

08:59.673 --> 09:01.275
Please, please. No!

09:02.309 --> 09:04.811
No! Ah!

09:13.320 --> 09:14.321
Get him up.

09:18.892 --> 09:20.727
Now take it out.

09:22.095 --> 09:23.263
- Ah!
- Do it!

09:37.244 --> 09:38.779
Next.

09:38.812 --> 09:40.013
<i>No, no, no.
Please don't. No, no, no.</i>

10:27.627 --> 10:28.962
This is utter madness.

10:28.996 --> 10:30.130
Mm?

10:41.241 --> 10:43.410
Oh, Catherine.

10:43.643 --> 10:45.078
Excellent news.

10:45.112 --> 10:46.713
The king has recovered.

10:46.747 --> 10:48.882
Come. Come and sit with us.

10:48.915 --> 10:50.917
Come.

10:54.121 --> 10:56.857
<i>The king has recovered.</i>

10:59.259 --> 11:01.795
Um... um, Francis,

11:01.828 --> 11:05.198
your father wants to toast you
on your wedding day.

11:05.232 --> 11:06.400
Excellent idea.

11:06.433 --> 11:07.868
Oh.

11:07.901 --> 11:09.002
He must rest.

11:09.036 --> 11:10.370
<i>Nonsense. He's well.</i>

11:12.706 --> 11:13.673
More wine.

11:13.707 --> 11:15.208
- No.
- <i>He's--he's well.</i>

11:15.242 --> 11:18.445
<i>He's--he's fine.
Ah, you're fine.</i>

11:21.715 --> 11:23.717
Ah...

11:23.750 --> 11:25.852
mm... music!

11:25.886 --> 11:28.722
Um, we must celebrate
the miracle.

11:33.427 --> 11:35.162
Ah.

11:35.195 --> 11:36.696
Oh. Oh. Oh.

11:38.031 --> 11:40.033
Um... he's fine.

11:40.067 --> 11:41.701
Ah, maybe Catherine is right.

11:41.735 --> 11:43.236
Eh? You must rest a little.

11:43.270 --> 11:45.439
Eh? Let me hold you.

11:45.472 --> 11:49.042
Oh.

11:49.076 --> 11:50.844
Henri.

11:55.382 --> 11:56.716
There.

11:58.418 --> 12:00.353
Perfect.

12:07.861 --> 12:09.463
Let me hold you. There.

12:09.496 --> 12:10.997
<i>Let me hold you.</i>

12:11.031 --> 12:13.233
<i>There. There. There.</i>

12:13.266 --> 12:15.802
There.

12:15.836 --> 12:17.304
Have some rest.

12:19.906 --> 12:22.008
That is fine.

12:23.376 --> 12:25.078
There is no pulse.

12:26.446 --> 12:28.748
No. He's well.

12:28.782 --> 12:30.250
Tell them.

12:30.283 --> 12:32.185
<i>He's well.</i>

12:32.219 --> 12:33.787
I'm sorry.

12:33.820 --> 12:36.790
No. He's fine.

12:36.823 --> 12:38.091
He's fine.

12:38.125 --> 12:39.493
<i>No.</i>

12:39.526 --> 12:41.795
<i>He's well.</i>

12:41.828 --> 12:43.363
<i>He's well. Ah?</i>

12:43.396 --> 12:44.531
<i>Henri.</i>

12:45.899 --> 12:48.135
<i>Henri.</i>

12:48.168 --> 12:50.170
<i>No. No.</i>

12:51.238 --> 12:53.006
No, Henri.

12:55.408 --> 12:57.344
You're not dead, my love.

12:57.377 --> 13:00.013
Don't leave me.

13:00.046 --> 13:01.314
Don't leave me alone.

13:02.482 --> 13:04.784
Don't leave me.

13:04.818 --> 13:06.853
Henri.

13:10.824 --> 13:12.492
Catherine.

13:14.060 --> 13:16.196
Help me, cousin.

13:16.229 --> 13:17.564
Help me.

13:19.399 --> 13:20.934
Cousin.

13:23.003 --> 13:26.106
Madame de Poitiers...

13:26.139 --> 13:28.475
the king is dead.

13:28.508 --> 13:31.912
<i>No.</i>

13:33.280 --> 13:35.182
<i>He's not dead.</i>

13:35.215 --> 13:37.350
He's fine.

13:37.384 --> 13:38.818
Please forgive me.

13:38.852 --> 13:40.353
Stay.

13:40.387 --> 13:43.123
Stay with me.

13:43.156 --> 13:44.591
<i>Please.</i>

13:44.824 --> 13:46.493
<i>Henri.</i>

13:46.526 --> 13:49.429
Don't look so glum.

13:49.462 --> 13:51.364
Your ship just came in.

13:51.398 --> 13:53.934
<i>What we had believed
to be one of God's miracles</i>

13:53.967 --> 13:56.369
<i>turned out to be a tragedy.</i>

13:59.039 --> 14:01.174
<i>Your mistress wanted
to blame her magician</i>

14:01.208 --> 14:02.842
<i>for her husband's death.</i>

14:02.876 --> 14:05.312
<i>But it was her own doing.</i>

14:05.345 --> 14:07.447
You lied to me!

14:07.480 --> 14:09.916
- Ugh.
- Ah!

14:09.950 --> 14:12.052
You said I had a choice!

14:12.085 --> 14:14.454
And I chose to keep him alive,
and yet he died!

14:14.487 --> 14:16.022
Tell me why he died. Tell me!

14:16.056 --> 14:18.525
Perhaps because he, like me,
does not believe in magic.

14:18.558 --> 14:21.962
He knew his death
was what you truly wanted.

14:21.995 --> 14:22.963
No!

14:22.996 --> 14:24.297
No, I didn't want it. I didn't!

14:24.331 --> 14:27.367
Yes, you did.

14:27.400 --> 14:30.237
Because you knew in death
he would belong to you

14:30.270 --> 14:32.939
as he never had in life.

14:35.909 --> 14:37.544
Ah.

14:41.548 --> 14:43.083
My child.

14:47.587 --> 14:50.023
You wanted to speak with me?

14:50.056 --> 14:52.292
I did. I do.

14:54.928 --> 14:56.396
How is the new king, hm?

14:56.429 --> 15:00.133
Well, he's...
overwhelmed by grief.

15:00.166 --> 15:03.370
- <i>Mm.</i>
- Understandably.

15:03.403 --> 15:06.673
Well, he's lucky he has you
when he's so reduced.

15:06.906 --> 15:09.342
I have sworn my loyalty
to him before God.

15:09.376 --> 15:11.311
Nothing can come between us.

15:11.344 --> 15:14.014
- Indeed.
- Yes, and on that subject,

15:14.047 --> 15:17.083
I believe that God
has chosen you and your husband

15:17.117 --> 15:18.985
for a reason.

15:19.019 --> 15:20.954
<i>Together, we can unite Europe</i>

15:20.987 --> 15:24.357
under the one true faith.

15:24.391 --> 15:26.059
Well, if it is my calling,
I shall answer.

15:26.092 --> 15:29.429
Oh, I very much believe
it is your calling, Mary,

15:29.462 --> 15:31.931
and I want to help you.

15:31.965 --> 15:35.502
But--but might the other
members of the Privy Council

15:35.535 --> 15:37.203
not object to such an alliance?

15:37.237 --> 15:39.172
Yes. They might.

15:39.205 --> 15:42.142
But you must remember
that anybody who opposes you

15:42.175 --> 15:43.977
is not to be trusted,

15:44.010 --> 15:46.546
<i>no matter what they profess
their beliefs to be.</i>

15:46.579 --> 15:48.548
Yes.

15:48.581 --> 15:51.251
If they oppose me,
they oppose the church itself.

15:51.284 --> 15:53.286
Exactly.

16:07.200 --> 16:09.602
The embalmers
removed the king's heart.

16:12.105 --> 16:13.306
So I took it.

16:30.056 --> 16:31.257
Drink.

16:38.264 --> 16:41.134
You will be his living tomb.

17:33.620 --> 17:34.788
<i>Hep.</i>

17:35.789 --> 17:37.390
<i>With the death of her husband,</i>

17:37.424 --> 17:39.292
<i>Catherine finally got
the revenge</i>

17:39.325 --> 17:41.494
<i>she had so long desired.</i>

17:47.600 --> 17:49.202
You still have me.

17:49.235 --> 17:51.471
I will never leave you.

17:51.504 --> 17:53.373
Don't say things
you don't mean.

18:15.562 --> 18:17.163
I should remind you that white

18:17.197 --> 18:18.565
is the traditional color
for mourning.

18:23.369 --> 18:25.238
I prefer black.

18:25.271 --> 18:27.273
Reminds people of their loss.

18:28.808 --> 18:31.444
Did Ruggieri tell you that?

18:31.478 --> 18:33.446
He did.

18:33.480 --> 18:35.381
I think it's time
you sent Ruggieri back

18:35.415 --> 18:37.150
to where he came from.

18:37.183 --> 18:38.518
Don't you?

18:40.186 --> 18:41.855
He makes you nervous.

18:41.888 --> 18:43.690
He makes me nervous
because he appeals

18:43.723 --> 18:46.226
to the darker parts
of your nature,

18:46.259 --> 18:48.428
which frighten me
far more than he does.

18:49.762 --> 18:51.297
The darker parts of my nature

18:51.331 --> 18:53.666
will always ensure
my survival...

18:55.535 --> 18:57.604
...and yours.

18:57.637 --> 19:00.173
Bit too soon to tell, isn't it?

19:21.661 --> 19:24.197
Your father always believed
in you.

19:25.565 --> 19:28.368
I know you will
do his memory justice.

19:28.401 --> 19:30.703
Thank you, Mother.

19:30.737 --> 19:32.772
I hope you're right.

19:32.805 --> 19:35.375
I don't doubt it.

19:49.322 --> 19:52.425
Grief suits you.

19:52.458 --> 19:54.928
It has enhanced
your natural beauty.

19:54.961 --> 19:57.864
I only wish I could stay and...

19:57.897 --> 20:00.667
get to know you better.

20:00.700 --> 20:02.535
Is that an appropriate way
to talk to me

20:02.569 --> 20:04.837
at my husband's funeral?

20:04.871 --> 20:06.573
Why not?

20:06.606 --> 20:08.675
You're no longer attached.

20:08.708 --> 20:10.843
And from what I hear,

20:10.877 --> 20:13.813
the marriage wasn't
a particularly happy one

20:13.846 --> 20:15.582
to begin with, hm?

20:17.684 --> 20:19.586
I thought I felt a little
something between us

20:19.619 --> 20:20.954
at the service.

20:22.522 --> 20:24.324
You were wrong.

20:24.357 --> 20:26.793
In fact, the thought
makes me physically ill.

20:26.826 --> 20:28.728
Hm.

20:28.761 --> 20:30.730
What a shame.

20:30.763 --> 20:32.632
The truth is,

20:32.665 --> 20:35.969
I always found funerals...

20:36.002 --> 20:38.471
vaguely erotic.

